            <thetext>A appearance theme currently defines three methods: setup, initial and state. All vWidget related stuff should be removed and should be implemented using states.

&quot;initial&quot; will be just a static hash map (instead of a function, which returns a hash map currently)
&quot;state&quot; will be have just one argument &quot;vState&quot; which is a hash map which contains the active states (like already). The vState will be converted into a string to use this string for caching the result of the function. With the next call of exactly the same combination of states it just returns the cached hash map.</thetext>
